claim.claim-text:
An agricultural sprayer (102), comprising:
a spraying system (254) that sprays a substance on an agricultural surface;
a crop characteristic sensor (230) that senses a crop characteristic of a crop on the agricultural surface and generates a crop characteristic signal indicative of the crop characteristic;
a spray control system (208) that identifies a position of a component of a crop plant based on the crop characteristic sensor signal; and
an action signal generator (346) that generates an action signal based on the identified position of the component of the crop plant.

An agricultural sprayer (102), comprising:
a spraying system (254) comprising a number of actuatable spray nozzles (112), the spraying system (254) configured to spray a substance on an agricultural surface;
a crop characteristic sensor (230) configured to sense a crop characteristic of a crop on the agricultural surface and to generate a crop characteristic signal indicative of the crop characteristic;
a spray control system (208) configured to identify a position of a component of a crop plant based on the crop characteristic sensor signal; and
an action signal generator (346) configured to generate an action signal based on the identified position of the component of the crop plant,
characterized in that the spray control system (208) is configured to identify a position of corn silks on a corn plant,
that the action signal generator (346) is configured to generate a first control signal that controls a position of at least one of the actuatable spray nozzles to spray the substance onto the identified position of the corn silk of the corn plant;
that the spray control system (208) further comprises a sprayer performance system (312) configured to receive, from a spray pattern sensor (238), a spray pattern sensor signal indicative of a coverage of the substance sprayed onto the identified position of the corn silks and generate a performance metric based on the coverage of the substance sprayed onto the identified position of the corn silks, and
that the action signal generator (346) is configured to generate a second control signal that adjusts the position of at least one of the actuatable spray nozzles (112) based on the coverage.
